PydanticAI
PydanticAI is a Python agent framework aimed at simplifying the process of developing production-grade applications with Generative AI.<SEP>PydanticAI is a Python agent framework designed to facilitate building production-grade applications with Generative AI technologies, streamlining the development process.<SEP>PydanticAI is a Python agent framework designed to facilitate the development of production-grade applications using Generative AI.

Agents
Agents in PydanticAI are autonomous entities that execute tasks using AI capabilities, designed to be integrated into applications for efficiency and effectiveness.<SEP>Agents refer to the entities or tools that operate within the PydanticAI framework, allowing for various tasks to be executed intelligently.<SEP>Agents refer to a category of tools and frameworks that can be used in conjunction with PydanticAI to build applications.

Model Providers
Model Providers are different AI model implementations that can be integrated within the PydanticAI framework for various uses.<SEP>Model Providers are various organizations or services that furnish the AI models compatible with the PydanticAI framework.<SEP>Model Providers refer to the different AI models used in conjunction with PydanticAI to power applications.<SEP>Model Providers represent a collection of different artificial intelligence models that can be leveraged within the PydanticAI framework.

MCP
MCP defines protocols for managing models effectively, which is a core function within PydanticAI.<SEP>MCP includes protocols for effectively managing AI models and their contexts within the PydanticAI framework.<SEP>Model Context Protocol (MCP) is a framework within PydanticAI for managing context in AI applications.

Graph
Graphs in PydanticAI are utilized for organizing information and functionalities internally.

Evals
Evals are mechanisms within PydanticAI for evaluating model performance.<SEP>Evals are used within PydanticAI to assess the performance and accuracy of AI models implemented in the framework.<SEP>Evals refer to evaluation tools within the PydanticAI ecosystem used to assess model performance.<SEP>Evals refer to the assessment tools within PydanticAI for evaluating the performance and effectiveness of AI models.
